<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Mrs Su-Fang Yu found adults feeding on leaves of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hayata" authorityYear="1913" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhododendron leptosanthum" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="leptosanthum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Rhododendron leptosanthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
July 3, 2009 in Chungchihkung, southern Taiwan. The first author and Mr. Mei-Hua Tsou found a number of larvae feeding tender leaves of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hayata" authorityYear="1911" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Ericaceae" genus="Vaccinium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vaccinium randaiense" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="randaiense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Vaccinium randaiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
May 9, 2011 in Tzuchung, southern Taiwan. These were reared in the laboratory. They began burrowing into soil May 12 and built underground chambers for pupation. The newly eclosed adults emerged from soil May 25.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">This species is widespread at mid-altitudes (1,500-2,500 m) in southern Taiwan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
